      <abstract>
        <p>Subcutaneous phaeohyphomycosis is an infection caused by dematiaceous fungi which
mainly affects immunosuppressed patients. We report a case of subcutaneous
phaeohyphomycosis on the back of the left hand in a kidney transplant patient who had
been taking prednisone, tacrolimus, and azathioprine daily for 3 years.</p>
      </abstract>
